Interface ClientCertificate

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ClientCertificateTypes, com.vmware.vapi.internal.bindings.CompletionStageService, com.vmware.vapi.bindings.Service
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ClientCertificateStub

    public interface ClientCertificate
extends com.vmware.vapi.bindings.Service, ClientCertificateTypes, com.vmware.vapi.internal.bindings.CompletionStageService
    The ClientCertificate interface provides methods to add and retrieve client certificate. This interface was added in vSphere API 7.0.0.0.

    • Method Detail

      • create

        ClientCertificate.CreateInvocation create(java.lang.String cluster,
                                          java.lang.String provider)
        Generate a new self signed client certificate. Existing client certificate is overwritten. The key server will use this certificate to validate the client connection. This method was added in vSphere API 7.0.0.0.
        Parameters:
        cluster - Identifier of the cluster. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: ClusterComputeResource.
        provider - Identifier of the provider. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: com.vmware.vcenter.trusted_infrastructure.trust_authority_clusters.kms.Provider.
        Returns:
        instance of ClientCertificate.CreateInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described create operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
        Throws:
        InvalidArgument - If cluster or provider id are empty.
        NotFound - If the cluster or provider is not found.
        Unauthenticated - If the caller is not authenticated.
        Error - If any other error occurs.

      • get

        ClientCertificate.GetInvocation get(java.lang.String cluster,
                                    java.lang.String provider)
        Return the existing client certificate. This method was added in vSphere API 7.0.0.0.

        Invocation Result:
        Client certificate, PEM.

        Returns:
        instance of ClientCertificate.GetInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described get operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
        Throws:
        InvalidArgument - If cluster or provider id are empty.
        NotFound - If the cluster or provider is not found.
        Unauthenticated - If the caller is not authenticated.
        Error - If any other error occurs.

      • update

        ClientCertificate.UpdateInvocation update(java.lang.String cluster,
                                          java.lang.String provider,
                                          ClientCertificateTypes.UpdateSpec spec)
        Update the client certificate.

        The key server will use this certificate to validate the client connection. If a client certificate already exists, it will be replaced.

        An optional private key can be specified if the certificate has already been provisioned.

        . This method was added in vSphere API 7.0.0.0.
        Parameters:
        cluster - Identifier of the cluster. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: ClusterComputeResource.
        provider - Identifier of the provider. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: com.vmware.vcenter.trusted_infrastructure.trust_authority_clusters.kms.Provider.
        spec - The update spec.
        Returns:
        instance of ClientCertificate.UpdateInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described update operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
        Throws:
        InvalidArgument - If the certificate or private key is invalid or cluster/provider id are empty.
        NotFound - If the cluster or provider is not found.
        Unauthenticated - If the caller is not authenticated.
        Error - If any other error occurs.
